author: Anonymous Poet
title: Re-Enrolled in Course; Unable to Hand in Pset 1
question:
Hello,

I don’t know where else to ask this, but last semester I was enrolled in CPSC 110 and I ended up dropping it. SPD doesn’t allow me to hand in Pset1 and says that my cwl is not accepted.

If any of the instructors know what I could do.

Thanks
student_answer:
Maybe check if your Computer Science Department account is still active? That might be the issue. Here's the link:
https://www.cs.ubc.ca/getacct
I'm not sure if you went through the set-up from the course syllabus, but there was a test file that was asked to be handed in to check that you're able to submit files via the SPD Hand-in. It might be a good idea to check if that works for you if you haven't done so already.
